  "text": "TbRI and TbRII have low affinity for each other, but in the presence of TGF-b, they bind together tightly [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Here, we coated ELISA plates with TbRI-Fc and examined the retention of TbRII-Fc when it was added in soluble form premixed (or not) with either TGF-b1 or Nrp1. As expected, TGF-b1 increased the retention of TbRII-Fc (Figure 2A) . Importantly, Nrp1-Fc also increased the retention of TbRII-Fc, and this occurred either in the presence or absence of TGF-b1 (Figure 2A ), although retention was slightly higher without the cytokine. These results provide evidence that Nrp1 is capable of",
